            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`.wsgi` isn't a real extension, it's really a `.py` file. Python only recognizes `.py` files as importable. Other files can be read in, compiled, then evaluated; but not imported.\r\n\r\n`flask` already detects `app.py` and `wsgi.py` automatically.\r\n\r\nTo handle other files, we'd need to either mess with `importlib` to make Python find and import other extensions, which I really don't think Flask should mess with. Or we'd need to tack on `read, compile, eval` to what is already a pretty complicated loading scheme."
        },
