            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Had a chat about this, appears to be an ancient holdover from when Apache CGI was in wide use. `mod_wsgi` kept the pattern even though it's not required, and everyone else followed suite. https://chat.stackoverflow.com/transcript/message/41855462#41855462\r\n\r\nIf you really want to keep the name, use a symlink to also name it `wsgi.py`."
